This is the heartwarming moment British tennis player Naomi Broady gets a kiss from her proud niece as she celebrates getting through to the second round at Wimbledon.

The 24-year-old was embraced by her four-year-old niece Lola-Rose after sealing her first-round victory over Hungarian Timea Babos.

British number four Broady, ranked 164 in the women's game, beat the world number 94 by two sets to one to seal her first ever grand slam victory.

